2. Electromagnetism
Page 272 — Fact Recall Questions
Q1 The strength of the magnetic field increases.
Q2 The further away from a wire you get, the weaker the
magnetic field is.
Q3 An electromagnet is a magnet whose magnetic field
can be turned on and off with an electric current.
Q4 E.g. magnetic separators in recycling plants / to hold
closed fridge doors / in cranes in scrapyards.

Q2 a) When current flows in the circuit, the
electromagnet has a magnetic field. The iron bolt

so it moves towards it, bolting the door.
